+
+- Goal: decide whether the mission admits one preferred exact-NS helical packet/sign object that is canonical enough to support later quantitative work, or whether the packet lift fails immediately at the canonicity gate.
+- What I tried: compared the new `SD_part` / `SD_target` proposal against the predecessor packet-object failure; re-read the inherited exact-NS packet notes and the sign-prototype sketch; then tested support/refinement, conjugate-pair representative choice, and desired-triad bookkeeping for invariance under harmless changes.
