The exploration closed with `canonicity failure`. The decisive issue is structural: `SD_part` cannot be made canonical on sign-closed support because counting both conjugates trivializes the global sign balance, while quotienting by conjugate pairs makes the value depend on an arbitrary representative choice. Even aside from that, `SD_target` and `Leak` still move with packet-support/refinement and desired-witness bookkeeping, so the new two-functional split sharpens the language without freezing one theorem-facing object.

